  "properties": {
    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "Instructions\r\n----\r\nThe <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">BackgroundPainter</code> class paints a multicolored background using a pattern.\r\n\r\n✅ **TO DO:** In <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">BackgroundPainter.java</code>, complete the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">paintMultiBackground()</code> method by writing a <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">for</code> loop that paints several rows in a repeating color pattern.\r\n\r\nEach row should be painted using <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">paintLine()</code> with the current color, then followed by <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">turnToNextRow()</code> to move down.\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background-color: #E0D1EC; border: 1px solid #9660bf; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 1.1em; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 10px;\">\r\n💡 <strong>TIP:</strong> Alternate or cycle through a few hardcoded colors using a loop and conditionals.\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n## ***Don't forget to . . .***\r\n![](https://images.code.org/eb2c8910ae2e150019b8e2177405d4af-image-1668191576873.png)\r\n\r\n## 🎯 Goal\r\n\r\n![](https://images.code.org/603d0ca0a5e44ee5a32b1ff26af73977-image-1674255983671.gif)\r\n",
    "mini_rubric": "false",
    "submittable": "false",
    "hide_share_and_remix": "true",
    "csa_view_mode": "neighborhood",
    "reference_links": [
      "/courses/csa-2023/guides/for-loops"
    ],
    "display_name": "The BackgroundPainter",
    "bubble_choice_description": "Convert the `while` loop to a `for` loop to paint a multicolored background in The Neighborhood.",
